The paper deals with the analysis of blockchain protocols, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). It also involves security and cryptography aspects, which are covered under Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The paper discusses the throughput and consistency of the protocols, which are related to Networked and Internet-based Systems (cs.NI). The analysis involves probabilistic guarantees, which are related to Information Theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper provides design references for public transaction ledger protocols, which falls under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
